 (success rc msg)‚ÜêExecUnderTrap expr;qdmx;valence;hasResult;cmd
‚çù Executes `expr` under a :Trap 0 and returns (1 0 '') in case of success and (0 ‚éïen <errorMessage>) otherwise.
‚çù If `expr` is a function that returns a result, that result will be ignored.
‚çù If `expr` is a function that requires a right argument, for the time bing ‚éïNULL is passed.
 :Trap 0
     hasResult‚Üê(10 ‚éïATX expr)‚àä1 ¬Ø1
     valence‚Üê11 ‚éïATX expr
     :If valence=0              ‚çù Niladic
         cmd‚Üê(hasResult/'{}'),expr
         ‚çécmd
     :ElseIf valence‚àä1 ¬Ø2       ‚çù Monadic or ambivalent
         cmd‚Üê(hasResult/'{}'),expr,' ‚éïNULL'
         ‚çécmd
     :Else                      ‚çù That leaves a dyadic call
         ‚çû‚Üê'>>> "lx" funcion ',expr,' is dyadic and therefore cannot called!',‚éïUCS 10
     :EndIf
     success‚Üê1
     rc‚Üê0
     msg‚Üê''
 :Else
     qdmx‚Üê‚éïDMX
     success‚Üê0
     rc‚Üêqdmx.EN
     msg‚Üêqdmx.DM
 :EndTrap
